No, apparently not. The creature just snarled and tried to fly directly towards Thassalin. Fortunately, Thassalin, despite his size, was agile enough to dodge, but Nyssi let out a scream as she almost lost her grip on Thassalin's extremely smooth scales.
"HOW CAN WE KILL HER?!", screamed Nyssi.
"AIM FOR THEIR HEADS!"
"THIS WILL BE DIFFICULT!"
Thassalin hissed and then drew a circle, moving closer to the mountain he called home. The dark beast followed, but became slightly panicked when a fire beam struck her from behind. She hadn't noticed she was no longer alone. She became even more panicked when Thassalin slowed down and then hurled his tail at her head, knocking her off course.
Roaring and snarling, it flew upward and spat into the air. Everything suddenly became dark, as if the monster had sucked the light from the sky and replaced it with a cloud of eternal night.
When he suddenly could no longer see anything, Thassalin attempted to retreat. He felt himself scraping along the tree tops before finally crashing into an open clearing. The beast seemed to know exactly where he had fallen and shot directly at him, dragging the black cloud with her.
"Kayel!" cried Tenuk as he slipped out of the cloud and began circling, searching for Nyssi and Thassalin in the darkness below. "What should we do now? Kayel…? Kayel, where are you?"
Nyssi struggled to her feet below. She was sure she had broken something, but her strange, supernatural healing powers were already beginning to take effect. Unfortunately, this did not apply to Thassalin. He leaned exhaustedly against the only tree that hadn't collapsed under his weight. Nyssi made every effort to get close to Thassalin, but she could barely see two meters ahead. Everything was pitch black and cloaked in eerie shadows. And within this darkness, something screamed and screeched.
A terrifying, armored tail crashed beside Nyssi to the ground and knocked her down. However, she noticed that the tail was just swinging wildly and not trying to hit her intentionally. The beast, or what little Nyssi could see and hear of it, snarled and clawed at the shadows it had created. Something shot through the darkness, struck at the monster, and confused it.
Suddenly, a gunshot cracked through the fog, and the monster fell silent, collapsed on the ground and remained motionless. The darkness around them faded and they saw what had happened: On the beast stood Kayel, holding his rifle heavily panting.
"That was... the craziest shadow jump I've ever made... Thanto kat'olon...", Kabel gasped for air. His eyes glowed almost black, and a dark energy circled his body. But while he was still speaking, color returned to his armor, and his eyes regained their normal yellow color.
It took a moment for Nyssi to understand what had happened. They had all known that Kayel possessed these strange shadow powers. He used them rarely, because most found them eerie and quite frightening. But Nyssi had not known that Kayel could use these powers in any kind of darkness. And as Kayel was behaving, he apparently was also quite surprised.
"Are you ok?" it broke out from Nyssi.
"Yes, I'm fine. I have killed something, I will be back to normal soon." Kayel looked at his work, while Tenuk flew down, landed beside him and resumed his normal spastic form.
Now that the beast was no longer moving, they could better see what it was. Its skin was pitch black and slimy, but the slime remained stuck to its body. It had four wings and four limbs, all ending in long, thin claws, and two straight horns stood out from its skull.
Before Tenuk and Kayel could ask what the hell they were looking at, something screeched and leaped out from a nearby bush. It didn't make it to them, because a familiar vehicle crashed into its side and caused the monster to slide to a stop in front of Nyssi's feet. Nyssi wanted to take no risks. She grabbed her shot gun, fired without thinking at its head, and the creature died right there.
“Oops…” murmured Retvik from the driver's seat before awkwardly turning off the engine and getting out of the truck. “Um, that wasn't really intended. Are you all okay?”
“You missed all the action,” scolded Tenuk. “Where were you?”
“You all just left me behind. I came as fast as I could…,” sighed Retvik. “May I ask what those terrible creatures are?”
Retvik's question was fortunately answered by Thassalin, who had recovered somewhat. He was covered in cuts and scratches and seemed a bit dazed, but not seriously injured.
"YOU HAVE KILLED THE CORRUPTED! THE INFECTED MONSTERS. CREATURES THAT WERE LEAVING HERE, AS THE CORRUPTION ATTACKED YOUR GODS."
"You mean the terrible God-Monster creature that we... helped to kill?" stuttered Tenuk.
"YES. EXACTLY THAT. Perhaps there are more. But I could not shoot in the head. I have no gun. And two against one is unfair, or?" Thassalin hobbled over to Kayel and patted his head. "THANK YOU, LITTLE ONE. YOU REMIND ME OF MY OLD FRIEND ARKADIN. JUST NOT SO MURDEROUS AND NOT SO SKILLED IN KILLING WHOLE UNIVERSES."
"Um... thank you... I think..." shrugged Kayel. "So, are we done here then?"
Nyssi shrugged her shoulders. She grabbed her camera and took a few photos of the now definitely dead creatures. Then she pulled out her favorite weapon, the ornate Death God dagger, and began cutting off one of the creature's horns. Afterwards, she moved on to the second. But as Nyssi was just finished, the creatures suddenly burst into flames and turned into a pile of ash in seconds. The same happened to the horns Nyssi had cut off.
"So, that's now both practical and impractical…", sighed Nyssi. "But at least I have the photos, hopefully."
